'''Space opera''' was a genre of science fiction in theater and comic book entertainment. The theater [[Five Star Entertainment]] located in the [[Depatar/Legends|City of Masks]] on [[Genarius]] performed a space opera named "[[A Rodian Love Story]]."

==Behind the scenes==
[[File:Planetstoriesclichecover.jpg|thumb|An example of real-world space opera]]
Space opera is a real-world subgenre of [[Wikipedia:science fiction|science fiction]] which is itself a genre of speculative fiction that emphasizes romantic adventure, exotic places, and larger-than-life characters in a galactic or intergalactic setting.

''[[Star Wars]]'' is typically characterized as belonging to the space opera genre, and many classic space opera serials such as [[Wikipedia:Flash Gordon|''Flash Gordon'']] and [[Wikipedia:Buck Rogers|''Buck Rogers'']] were among the impressions that inspired [[George Lucas]] into making the Star Wars movies.

The further [[Star Wars Legends|expansion]] of the ''Star Wars'' universe carries on the tradition of space opera beyond the films.

